"title": "7426: ritual washing",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7426",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The act of washing for consecration or for purification from uncleanness. It involved washing all or part of the body or one's clothing. Jesus Christ's attitude to the Pharisees reflected, not a disavowal of ritual washing, but disapproval of their emphasis on the outward, rather than inward, forms of religion.</p>\n<h2>Ritual washing for consecration</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:10-Exod19:11\">EXO 19:10–19:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:14\">EXO 19:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:12-Exod40:15\">EXO 40:12–40:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:5-Num8:7\">NUM 8:5–8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:21-Num8:22\">NUM 8:21–8:22</a></p>\n<h2>Ritual washing for cleansing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:15\">LEV 17:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:6\">LEV 13:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:34\">LEV 13:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:16-Lev15:18\">LEV 15:16–15:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:21-Lev15:23\">LEV 15:21–15:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:10\">NUM 19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:19\">NUM 19:19</a></p>\n<h2>Methods of ritual washing</h2>\n<h3>Washing clothes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:24\">NUM 31:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:27\">LEV 6:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:24-Lev11:28\">LEV 11:24–11:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:39-Lev11:40\">LEV 11:39–11:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:58\">LEV 13:58</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:43-Lev14:47\">LEV 14:43–14:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:21\">NUM 19:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:14\">REV 7:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:14\">REV 22:14</a></p>\n<h3>Bathing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:8-Lev14:9\">LEV 14:8–14:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:4-Lev15:13\">LEV 15:4–15:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:27\">LEV 15:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:26-Lev16:28\">LEV 16:26–16:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:15\">LEV 17:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:7-Num19:8\">NUM 19:7–19:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:9-Deut23:11\">DEU 23:9–23:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:9-2Kgs5:14\">2KI 5:9–5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:7\">PSA 51:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:19-Heb10:22\">HEB 10:19–10:22</a></p>\n<h3>Sprinkling with the water of purification</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:17-Num19:19\">NUM 19:17–19:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:5-Num8:7\">NUM 8:5–8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:13\">NUM 19:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:24-Ezek36:25\">EZK 36:24–36:25</a></p>\n<h3>Washing hands and feet</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:17-Exod30:21\">EXO 30:17–30:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:30-Exod40:32\">EXO 40:30–40:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:6-Deut21:9\">DEU 21:6–21:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:5-John13:10\">JHN 13:5–13:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:8\">JAS 4:8</a></p>\n<h2>Consequences of the failure to perform ritual washing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:20\">NUM 19:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:15-Lev17:16\">LEV 17:15–17:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:13\">NUM 19:13</a></p>\n<h2>The NT perception of ritual washing</h2>\n<h3>It was practised in NT times</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:6\">JHN 2:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:25\">JHN 3:25</a></p>\n<h3>The Pharisees over-emphasised its importance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:1-Matt15:11\">MAT 15:1–15:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:1-Mark7:23\">MRK 7:1–7:23</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:37-Luke11:41\">LUK 11:37–11:41</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's atoning work rendered it unnecessary</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:6-Heb9:14\">HEB 9:6–9:14</a></strong></p>",
